&lt;p&gt;What would be the word on the opposite side of &amp;#39;Feb&amp;#39; if the given sheet is folded to form a cube?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/24/09/F2_Savira_SSC_4-9-24_D1.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 177px; height: 186px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The faces opposite to each other are shown below:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/24/09/F2_Savira_SSC_4-9-24_D2.png&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41); width: 193px; height: 205px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; As the alternate positions become opposite to each other,&amp;nbsp;the remaining two faces become opposite to each other.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;So, opposite pairs are:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Mar &amp;rarr; Apr&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;May &amp;rarr; Feb&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Jan &amp;rarr; June&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Therefore, &amp;#39;May&amp;#39; is the opposite of &amp;#39;Feb&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Hence,&lt;strong&gt; Option 4:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;May&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the correct answer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Given Equation:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;44 F 18 C 3 B 108 D 6 = ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;BODMAS Rule:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/07/62b6b038309f241e4e39e3b7_16572638863551.png&quot; style=&quot;height: 201px; width: 363px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Decoding the given information:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width: 200px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;thead&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;th scope=&quot;col&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Alphabet&lt;/th&gt;
			&lt;th scope=&quot;col&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;F&lt;/th&gt;
			&lt;th scope=&quot;col&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;C&lt;/th&gt;
			&lt;th scope=&quot;col&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;D&lt;/th&gt;
			&lt;th scope=&quot;col&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;B&lt;/th&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/thead&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meaning&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;-&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;times;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;divide;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;+&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Now replacing the sign from left to right using BODMAS Rule, we get:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 44 - 18 &amp;times; 3 + &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;108 &amp;divide; 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; 44 - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;18 &amp;times; 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; + 18&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;44&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; - 54 &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;+ 18&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;62&amp;nbsp;- 54&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 8&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Hence, the correct option is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Option 1&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Consider the following arrangement&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2 3 A 3 9 D J O 2 8 3 B I N 7 8 9 E&amp;nbsp;B 7 8 9 2 0 G O 2 3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If all the vowels are removed from the above&amp;nbsp;arrangement which element will be third to the right of fifth element from the left?&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(77, 81, 86); &quot;&gt;A&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold; &quot;&gt;vowel&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(77, 81, 86); &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a syllabic speech sound pronounced without any stricture in the vocal tract.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold; &quot;&gt;Vowels&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(77, 81, 86); &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;are the letters A, E, I, O, and U . The other letters in the alphabet are called consonants.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(77, 81, 86); &quot;&gt;The given arrangement:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2 3 A 3 9 D J O&amp;nbsp;2 8 3 B I N 7 8 9 E&amp;nbsp;B 7 8 9 2 0 G O 2 3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If we remove Vowels i.e. A, E, I, O and U.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2 3&lt;strong&gt; A &lt;/strong&gt;3 9 D J &lt;strong&gt;O&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;2 8 3 B &lt;strong&gt;I &lt;/strong&gt;N 7 8 9 &lt;strong&gt;E&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;B 7 8 9 2 0 G &lt;strong&gt;O&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;2 3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So,&amp;nbsp; the remaining arrangement:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2 3&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;3 9 &lt;strong&gt;D&lt;/strong&gt; J&amp;nbsp;2 &lt;strong&gt;8&lt;/strong&gt; 3 B&amp;nbsp;N 7 8 9&amp;nbsp;B 7 8 9 2 0 G 2 3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The 5th element from left is &lt;strong&gt;D.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;The&amp;nbsp;third to the right of 5 fifth position from the left is&lt;strong&gt; 8&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence &lt;strong&gt;option 4&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As no information about the direction is given, we can assume any direction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let us assume that Yoga traveled from point E to F for 7 km towards the north and then he turned right i.e. towards the east and went for 8 km and then again turned right i.e. towards the south and went for 7 km and then finally turned left i.e. towards the east.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The path covered by Yoga is shown below:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/21/07/DD03209.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 499px; height: 404px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The distance between E and I = 8 + 3 = &lt;strong&gt;11 km&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the distance between the starting and the final point is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;11 km&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
